{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":512,"text":"I'd like to tell you about two games of chess."},{"time":3068,"text":"The first happened in 1997, in which Garry Kasparov,"},{"time":6932,"text":"a human, lost to Deep Blue, a machine."},{"time":10648,"text":"To many, this was the dawn of a new era,"},{"time":12888,"text":"one where man would be dominated by machine."},{"time":15667,"text":"But here we are, 20 years on, and the greatest change"},{"time":19001,"text":"in how we relate to computers is the iPad,"},{"time":21691,"text":"not HAL."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23736,"text":"The second game was a freestyle chess tournament"},{"time":26384,"text":"in 2005, in which man and machine could enter together"},{"time":29353,"text":"as partners, rather than adversaries, if they so chose."},{"time":34019,"text":"At first, the results were predictable."},{"time":35870,"text":"Even a supercomputer was beaten by a grandmaster"},{"time":38367,"text":"with a relatively weak laptop."},{"time":40679,"text":"The surprise came at the end. Who won?"},{"time":43664,"text":"Not a grandmaster with a supercomputer,"},{"time":46440,"text":"but actually two American amateurs"},{"time":47933,"text":"using three relatively weak laptops."},{"time":51755,"text":"Their ability to coach and manipulate their computers"},{"time":54351,"text":"to deeply explore specific positions"},{"time":56786,"text":"effectively counteracted the superior chess knowledge"},{"time":59176,"text":"of the grandmasters and the superior computational power"},{"time":61785,"text":"of other adversaries."},{"time":63694,"text":"This is an astonishing result: average men,"},{"time":66599,"text":"average machines beating the best man, the best machine."},{"time":70680,"text":"And anyways, isn't it supposed to be man versus machine?"},{"time":73879,"text":"Instead, it's about cooperation, and the right type of cooperation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78031,"text":"We've been paying a lot of attention to Marvin Minsky's"},{"time":80888,"text":"vision for artificial intelligence over the last 50 years."},{"time":84130,"text":"It's a sexy vision, for sure. Many have embraced it."},{"time":86392,"text":"It's become the dominant school of thought in computer science."},{"time":89145,"text":"But as we enter the era of big data, of network systems,"},{"time":92217,"text":"of open platforms, and embedded technology,"},{"time":94915,"text":"I'd like to suggest it's time to reevaluate an alternative vision"},{"time":98307,"text":"that was actually developed around the same time."},{"time":101377,"text":"I'm talking about J.C.R. Licklider's human-computer symbiosis,"},{"time":104709,"text":"perhaps better termed \"intelligence augmentation,\" I.A."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108517,"text":"Licklider was a computer science titan who had a profound"},{"time":111157,"text":"effect on the development of technology and the Internet."},{"time":114163,"text":"His vision was to enable man and machine to cooperate"},{"time":117031,"text":"in making decisions, controlling complex situations"},{"time":120621,"text":"without the inflexible dependence"},{"time":122391,"text":"on predetermined programs."},{"time":124924,"text":"Note that word \"cooperate.\""},{"time":127422,"text":"Licklider encourages us not to take a toaster"},{"time":130169,"text":"and make it Data from \"Star Trek,\""},{"time":132453,"text":"but to take a human and make her more capable."},{"time":135988,"text":"Humans are so amazing -- how we think,"},{"time":137899,"text":"our non-linear approaches, our creativity,"},{"time":140517,"text":"iterative hypotheses, all very difficult if possible at all"},{"time":142648,"text":"for computers to do."},{"time":143993,"text":"Licklider intuitively realized this, contemplating humans"},{"time":146445,"text":"setting the goals, formulating the hypotheses,"},{"time":148772,"text":"determining the criteria, and performing the evaluation."},{"time":152148,"text":"Of course, in other ways, humans are so limited."},{"time":153923,"text":"We're terrible at scale, computation and volume."},{"time":157158,"text":"We require high-end talent management"},{"time":158994,"text":"to keep the rock band together and playing."},{"time":161058,"text":"Licklider foresaw computers doing all the routinizable work"},{"time":163262,"text":"that was required to prepare the way for insights and decision making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166538,"text":"Silently, without much fanfare,"},{"time":168762,"text":"this approach has been compiling victories beyond chess."},{"time":172116,"text":"Protein folding, a topic that shares the incredible expansiveness of chess â€”"},{"time":175472,"text":"there are more ways of folding a protein than there are atoms in the universe."},{"time":178514,"text":"This is a world-changing problem with huge implications"},{"time":180867,"text":"for our ability to understand and treat disease."},{"time":183175,"text":"And for this task, supercomputer field brute force simply isn't enough."},{"time":187423,"text":"Foldit, a game created by computer scientists,"},{"time":189807,"text":"illustrates the value of the approach."},{"time":192309,"text":"Non-technical, non-biologist amateurs play a video game"},{"time":195350,"text":"in which they visually rearrange the structure of the protein,"},{"time":198423,"text":"allowing the computer to manage the atomic forces"},{"time":199922,"text":"and interactions and identify structural issues."},{"time":202879,"text":"This approach beat supercomputers 50 percent of the time"},{"time":205902,"text":"and tied 30 percent of the time."},{"time":208486,"text":"Foldit recently made a notable and major scientific discovery"},{"time":211623,"text":"by deciphering the structure of the Mason-Pfizer monkey virus."},{"time":214783,"text":"A protease that had eluded determination for over 10 years"},{"time":217798,"text":"was solved was by three players in a matter of days,"},{"time":220424,"text":"perhaps the first major scientific advance"},{"time":222449,"text":"to come from playing a video game."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224772,"text":"Last year, on the site of the Twin Towers,"},{"time":226953,"text":"the 9/11 memorial opened."},{"time":228426,"text":"It displays the names of the thousands of victims"},{"time":231147,"text":"using a beautiful concept called \"meaningful adjacency.\""},{"time":234210,"text":"It places the names next to each other based on their"},{"time":236376,"text":"relationships to one another: friends, families, coworkers."},{"time":238589,"text":"When you put it all together, it's quite a computational"},{"time":241617,"text":"challenge: 3,500 victims, 1,800 adjacency requests,"},{"time":245840,"text":"the importance of the overall physical specifications"},{"time":248932,"text":"and the final aesthetics."},{"time":251069,"text":"When first reported by the media, full credit for such a feat"},{"time":253684,"text":"was given to an algorithm from the New York City"},{"time":255576,"text":"design firm Local Projects. The truth is a bit more nuanced."},{"time":259577,"text":"While an algorithm was used to develop the underlying framework,"},{"time":262448,"text":"humans used that framework to design the final result."},{"time":265456,"text":"So in this case, a computer had evaluated millions"},{"time":267681,"text":"of possible layouts, managed a complex relational system,"},{"time":271016,"text":"and kept track of a very large set of measurements"},{"time":273430,"text":"and variables, allowing the humans to focus"},{"time":275840,"text":"on design and compositional choices."},{"time":278642,"text":"So the more you look around you,"},{"time":279678,"text":"the more you see Licklider's vision everywhere."},{"time":281640,"text":"Whether it's augmented reality in your iPhone or GPS in your car,"},{"time":284944,"text":"human-computer symbiosis is making us more capable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287914,"text":"So if you want to improve human-computer symbiosis,"},{"time":289569,"text":"what can you do?"},{"time":290998,"text":"You can start by designing the human into the process."},{"time":293450,"text":"Instead of thinking about what a computer will do to solve the problem,"},{"time":295654,"text":"design the solution around what the human will do as well."},{"time":299523,"text":"When you do this, you'll quickly realize that you spent"},{"time":301460,"text":"all of your time on the interface between man and machine,"},{"time":304339,"text":"specifically on designing away the friction in the interaction."},{"time":307438,"text":"In fact, this friction is more important than the power"},{"time":310204,"text":"of the man or the power of the machine"},{"time":312256,"text":"in determining overall capability."},{"time":314187,"text":"That's why two amateurs with a few laptops"},{"time":316164,"text":"handily beat a supercomputer and a grandmaster."},{"time":318620,"text":"What Kasparov calls process is a byproduct of friction."},{"time":321625,"text":"The better the process, the less the friction."},{"time":324026,"text":"And minimizing friction turns out to be the decisive variable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328282,"text":"Or take another example: big data."},{"time":330525,"text":"Every interaction we have in the world is recorded"},{"time":332431,"text":"by an ever growing array of sensors: your phone,"},{"time":335490,"text":"your credit card, your computer. The result is big data,"},{"time":337863,"text":"and it actually presents us with an opportunity"},{"time":339605,"text":"to more deeply understand the human condition."},{"time":342267,"text":"The major emphasis of most approaches to big data"},{"time":344572,"text":"focus on, \"How do I store this data? How do I search"},{"time":346787,"text":"this data? How do I process this data?\""},{"time":349063,"text":"These are necessary but insufficient questions."},{"time":351267,"text":"The imperative is not to figure out how to compute,"},{"time":353738,"text":"but what to compute. How do you impose human intuition"},{"time":355922,"text":"on data at this scale?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":357713,"text":"Again, we start by designing the human into the process."},{"time":361212,"text":"When PayPal was first starting as a business, their biggest"},{"time":364024,"text":"challenge was not, \"How do I send money back and forth online?\""},{"time":366828,"text":"It was, \"How do I do that without being defrauded by organized crime?\""},{"time":370700,"text":"Why so challenging? Because while computers can learn"},{"time":372788,"text":"to detect and identify fraud based on patterns,"},{"time":375932,"text":"they can't learn to do that based on patterns"},{"time":377411,"text":"they've never seen before, and organized crime"},{"time":379527,"text":"has a lot in common with this audience: brilliant people,"},{"time":382236,"text":"relentlessly resourceful, entrepreneurial spirit â€” (Laughter) â€”"},{"time":385876,"text":"and one huge and important difference: purpose."},{"time":388588,"text":"And so while computers alone can catch all but the cleverest"},{"time":391420,"text":"fraudsters, catching the cleverest is the difference"},{"time":393673,"text":"between success and failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396218,"text":"There's a whole class of problems like this, ones with"},{"time":398439,"text":"adaptive adversaries. They rarely if ever present with a"},{"time":401014,"text":"repeatable pattern that's discernable to computers."},{"time":403750,"text":"Instead, there's some inherent component of innovation or disruption,"},{"time":407743,"text":"and increasingly these problems are buried in big data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410478,"text":"For example, terrorism. Terrorists are always adapting"},{"time":412978,"text":"in minor and major ways to new circumstances, and despite"},{"time":415030,"text":"what you might see on TV, these adaptations,"},{"time":418124,"text":"and the detection of them, are fundamentally human."},{"time":420417,"text":"Computers don't detect novel patterns and new behaviors,"},{"time":423534,"text":"but humans do. Humans, using technology, testing hypotheses,"},{"time":426769,"text":"searching for insight by asking machines to do things for them."},{"time":431389,"text":"Osama bin Laden was not caught by artificial intelligence."},{"time":433709,"text":"He was caught by dedicated, resourceful, brilliant people"},{"time":436262,"text":"in partnerships with various technologies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440531,"text":"As appealing as it might sound, you cannot algorithmically"},{"time":443349,"text":"data mine your way to the answer."},{"time":444950,"text":"There is no \"Find Terrorist\" button, and the more data"},{"time":447805,"text":"we integrate from a vast variety of sources"},{"time":450107,"text":"across a wide variety of data formats from very"},{"time":452240,"text":"disparate systems, the less effective data mining can be."},{"time":455549,"text":"Instead, people will have to look at data"},{"time":457573,"text":"and search for insight, and as Licklider foresaw long ago,"},{"time":461029,"text":"the key to great results here is the right type of cooperation,"},{"time":463714,"text":"and as Kasparov realized,"},{"time":465238,"text":"that means minimizing friction at the interface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468269,"text":"Now this approach makes possible things like combing"},{"time":471027,"text":"through all available data from very different sources,"},{"time":474413,"text":"identifying key relationships and putting them in one place,"},{"time":477205,"text":"something that's been nearly impossible to do before."},{"time":480133,"text":"To some, this has terrifying privacy and civil liberties"},{"time":482075,"text":"implications. To others it foretells of an era of greater"},{"time":485485,"text":"privacy and civil liberties protections,"},{"time":487394,"text":"but privacy and civil liberties are of fundamental importance."},{"time":490330,"text":"That must be acknowledged, and they can't be swept aside,"},{"time":492523,"text":"even with the best of intents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495053,"text":"So let's explore, through a couple of examples, the impact"},{"time":497571,"text":"that technologies built to drive human-computer symbiosis"},{"time":499977,"text":"have had in recent time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502896,"text":"In October, 2007, U.S. and coalition forces raided"},{"time":506312,"text":"an al Qaeda safe house in the city of Sinjar"},{"time":508728,"text":"on the Syrian border of Iraq."},{"time":510662,"text":"They found a treasure trove of documents:"},{"time":513038,"text":"700 biographical sketches of foreign fighters."},{"time":515373,"text":"These foreign fighters had left their families in the Gulf,"},{"time":517957,"text":"the Levant and North Africa to join al Qaeda in Iraq."},{"time":521103,"text":"These records were human resource forms."},{"time":522719,"text":"The foreign fighters filled them out as they joined the organization."},{"time":525574,"text":"It turns out that al Qaeda, too,"},{"time":526785,"text":"is not without its bureaucracy. (Laughter)"},{"time":529382,"text":"They answered questions like, \"Who recruited you?\""},{"time":531480,"text":"\"What's your hometown?\" \"What occupation do you seek?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":534334,"text":"In that last question, a surprising insight was revealed."},{"time":537503,"text":"The vast majority of foreign fighters"},{"time":539903,"text":"were seeking to become suicide bombers for martyrdom --"},{"time":542303,"text":"hugely important, since between 2003 and 2007, Iraq"},{"time":546641,"text":"had 1,382 suicide bombings, a major source of instability."},{"time":550885,"text":"Analyzing this data was hard. The originals were sheets"},{"time":552943,"text":"of paper in Arabic that had to be scanned and translated."},{"time":555685,"text":"The friction in the process did not allow for meaningful"},{"time":557877,"text":"results in an operational time frame using humans, PDFs"},{"time":561227,"text":"and tenacity alone."},{"time":563445,"text":"The researchers had to lever up their human minds"},{"time":565398,"text":"with technology to dive deeper, to explore non-obvious"},{"time":567743,"text":"hypotheses, and in fact, insights emerged."},{"time":570961,"text":"Twenty percent of the foreign fighters were from Libya,"},{"time":573605,"text":"50 percent of those from a single town in Libya,"},{"time":576573,"text":"hugely important since prior statistics put that figure at"},{"time":579023,"text":"three percent. It also helped to hone in on a figure"},{"time":581406,"text":"of rising importance in al Qaeda, Abu Yahya al-Libi,"},{"time":584383,"text":"a senior cleric in the Libyan Islamic fighting group."},{"time":587014,"text":"In March of 2007, he gave a speech, after which there was"},{"time":589678,"text":"a surge in participation amongst Libyan foreign fighters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593144,"text":"Perhaps most clever of all, though, and least obvious,"},{"time":596250,"text":"by flipping the data on its head, the researchers were"},{"time":598323,"text":"able to deeply explore the coordination networks in Syria"},{"time":601223,"text":"that were ultimately responsible for receiving and"},{"time":603740,"text":"transporting the foreign fighters to the border."},{"time":606204,"text":"These were networks of mercenaries, not ideologues,"},{"time":608837,"text":"who were in the coordination business for profit."},{"time":611235,"text":"For example, they charged Saudi foreign fighters"},{"time":613139,"text":"substantially more than Libyans, money that would have"},{"time":615338,"text":"otherwise gone to al Qaeda."},{"time":617658,"text":"Perhaps the adversary would disrupt their own network"},{"time":619703,"text":"if they knew they cheating would-be jihadists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":622738,"text":"In January, 2010, a devastating 7.0 earthquake struck Haiti,"},{"time":626483,"text":"third deadliest earthquake of all time, left one million people,"},{"time":629399,"text":"10 percent of the population, homeless."},{"time":631983,"text":"One seemingly small aspect of the overall relief effort"},{"time":635120,"text":"became increasingly important as the delivery of food"},{"time":637296,"text":"and water started rolling."},{"time":639456,"text":"January and February are the dry months in Haiti,"},{"time":640914,"text":"yet many of the camps had developed standing water."},{"time":643856,"text":"The only institution with detailed knowledge of Haiti's"},{"time":645978,"text":"floodplains had been leveled"},{"time":647275,"text":"in the earthquake, leadership inside."},{"time":650283,"text":"So the question is, which camps are at risk,"},{"time":652858,"text":"how many people are in these camps, what's the"},{"time":654779,"text":"timeline for flooding, and given very limited resources"},{"time":657090,"text":"and infrastructure, how do we prioritize the relocation?"},{"time":660474,"text":"The data was incredibly disparate. The U.S. Army had"},{"time":662818,"text":"detailed knowledge for only a small section of the country."},{"time":665747,"text":"There was data online from a 2006 environmental risk"},{"time":668258,"text":"conference, other geospatial data, none of it integrated."},{"time":670922,"text":"The human goal here was to identify camps for relocation"},{"time":673880,"text":"based on priority need."},{"time":676275,"text":"The computer had to integrate a vast amount of geospacial"},{"time":678715,"text":"information, social media data and relief organization"},{"time":681299,"text":"information to answer this question."},{"time":684779,"text":"By implementing a superior process, what was otherwise"},{"time":687194,"text":"a task for 40 people over three months became"},{"time":689802,"text":"a simple job for three people in 40 hours,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":692978,"text":"all victories for human-computer symbiosis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695606,"text":"We're more than 50 years into Licklider's vision"},{"time":697660,"text":"for the future, and the data suggests that we should be"},{"time":699902,"text":"quite excited about tackling this century's hardest problems,"},{"time":702932,"text":"man and machine in cooperation together."},{"time":705879,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":708076,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}